<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>System Atlas // Production Template</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin="">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;700&display=swap">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/pavelzosim/atlas-framework@master/cdn/atlas-framework.css">

    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/prism.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/components/prism-c.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/prism/1.29.0/components/prism-glsl.min.js"></script>

    <style>
        *, *::before, *::after {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        html, body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            overflow: hidden; /* Прячем скроллбары самого iframe-контейнера Wix */
            background: transparent;
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Courier New', monospace !important;
        }

        h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, p, span, div, li, td, th {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Courier New', monospace !important;
        }

        .atlas-container {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 16px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="atlas-container">

        <header id="site-passport"></header>

        <main id="atlas-body">
            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>1. Unity ShaderLab Cheatsheet – Introduction</h2>
                <p>This Unity ShaderLab cheatsheet provides a structured, production-oriented reference for technical artists working with hand-written shaders in Unity.
                Whether you’re transitioning from ShaderGraph or diving into hand-written shaders, this guide provides you with an in-depth look at shader code structure, property declaration, and how the GPU processes shader code.
                We’ll also explore special ShaderLab features such as drawer attributes, tags, and SubShaders, and discuss how these concepts vary across render pipelines (Built-in, URP, HDRP).</p>             
                
                <h2> Unity ShaderLab Cheatsheet: What is ShaderLab in Unity? </h2>
                <p> ShaderLab is Unity’s shader definition language used to structure passes, render states and connect CG/HLSL code. </p>

                <div class="atlas-compare">
                    
                    <div class="atlas-compare__column">
                        <div class="atlas-compare__badge" data-side="left">// SYSTEM_CORE: CG_HLSL_PROGRAM</div>
                        <div class="atlas-compare__content">
                            <span class="atlas-compare__concept">CG Shader</span>
                            <p>Uses the Cg/HLSL language to write low-level shader programs. A shader file typically contains execution sections enclosed by <code>CGPROGRAM</code> and <code>ENDCG</code> (or modern <code>HLSLPROGRAM</code> blocks for URP/HDRP) that are compiled directly into raw GPU bytecode instructions.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="atlas-compare__divider"></div>
                    
                    <div class="atlas-compare__column">
                        <div class="atlas-compare__badge" data-side="right">// SYSTEM_WRAPPER: SHADERLAB_PIPELINE</div>
                        <div class="atlas-compare__content">
                            <span class="atlas-compare__concept">ShaderLab</span>
                            <p>A Unity-specific declarative wrapper that defines properties, SubShaders, passes, and fallback states. It orchestrates how your low-level program interacts with the material Inspector UI and binds to the internal rendering execution pipeline.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>


                <div class="content-block">
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>CG Shader:</b> Вычисление локальных координат меша.</li>
                        <li><b>Buffer Residency Control:</b> Контроль нахождения дескрипторов в памяти.</li>
                        <li><b>Asynchronous Compute Layers:</b> Вынос тяжелых проходов в параллельные очереди.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>Пошаговый процесс деплоя шейдера:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Объявление глобальных свойств в блоке Properties.</li>
                        <li>Привязка константных буферов (CBUFFER) внутри HLSLPROGRAM.</li>
                        <li>Конфигурация проходов рендеринга и стейтов растеризатора.</li>
                    </ol>

                </div>

                <div class="atlas-section-break" data-index="x1"></div>
                
                <h2>2. How ShaderLab Works with CG and HLSL in Unity</h2>
                
                <div class="atlas-section-break" data-index="x2"></div>

                <h2>3. Shader Declaration & Properties in ShaderLab</h2>
                <p>Общее описание структуры шейдера и синтаксиса блоков разметки Unity.</p>

                <h3>3.1 Defining the Shader Name (Inspector Path)</h3>
                <p>The shader name determines its hierarchical location in the Unity shader dropdown menus.</p>

                <h3>3.2 Properties Syntax & Data Types</h3>
                <p>Within the shader declaration, the Properties block allows you to expose parameters to the user. The basic syntax for each property is:</p>

                <h4>3.2.1 Numeric Data Types</h4>
                <p>Numeric Data Types - These properties control scalar values such as factors, intensity, or other numerical parameters. <code>float</code>, <code>half</code>, <code>int</code>.</p>

                <h4>3.2.2 Vector & Color Types</h4>
                <p>Здесь будут описаны векторы (Vector) и палитры цвета (Color) для передачи массивов float4.</p>

                <h4>3.2.3 Texture Types</h4>
                <p>Синтаксис подключения текстурных карт (2D, Cube, 3D, 2DArray) и генерация их сэмплеров.</p>

                <h3>3.3 ShaderLab Attribute Drawers</h3>
                <p>Специальные атрибуты отрисовки интерфейса инспектора материалов в Unity.</p>

                <div class="atlas-section-break" data-index="x3"></div>

                <div class="atlas-eof-divider">
                    <span class="atlas-eof-divider__line"></span>
                    <span class="atlas-eof-divider__meta">// END OF SESSION // EOF</span>
                    <span class="atlas-eof-divider__line"></span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <footer id="site-footer"></footer>

    </div>

    <script>
        /* ==========================================================================
        ── КОНФИГУРАЦИЯ ПОСТА (Заполняется вручную для каждого лога)
        ========================================================================== */
        var CONFIG = {
            user:       'pavelzosim',
            path:       '~',
            command:    'cat unity_shaderlab_cheatsheet.log',

            prefix:     'SYSTEM_ATLAS // R&D_LOG',
            project:    'UNITY_SHADERLAB',
            module:     'shaders',
            version:    '1.3.2',
            logId:      '#042',
            status:     'EDUCATIONAL',

            slug:       'unity-shaderlab-cheatsheet',

            author:     '...',
            created:    '----.--.--',
            modified:   null,
            wordCount:  null,
            title:      null,
            tags:       [],

            tagBaseUrl: 'https://www.pavelzosim.com/blog/tags/'
        };

        // Эндпоинты данных
        var BACKEND_URL = 'https://www.pavelzosim.com/_functions/getPostData';
        var FOOTER_URL  = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/pavelzosim/atlas-framework@master/cdn/atlas-site-footer-config.json?v=' + new Date().getTime();

        /* ==========================================================================
        ── СЛУЖЕБНАЯ ЛОГИКА WIX (Динамический расчёт высоты iFrame)
        ========================================================================== */
        function sendPostHeight(reason) {
            var height = document.documentElement.scrollHeight || document.body.scrollHeight;
            window.parent.postMessage({
                type: 'resize',
                height: height
            }, '*');
            console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] Height sent to Wix: " + height + "px | Reason: " + reason);
        }

        window.addEventListener('resize', function() {
            sendPostHeight("Window resized");
        });

        /* ==========================================================================
        ── АВТОМАТИЧЕСКИЙ ПАРСИНГ КОДА (Prism Engine)
        ========================================================================== */
        function processCodeBlocks() {
            console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] Scanning DOM for code blocks...");
            if (typeof Prism !== 'undefined') {
                var blocks = document.querySelectorAll('#atlas-body pre code');
                if (blocks.length > 0) {
                    console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] Found " + blocks.length + " code block(s). Executing Prism...");
                    
                    var processedCount = 0;
                    blocks.forEach(function(el) {
                        Prism.highlightElement(el, false, function() {
                            processedCount++;
                            if (processedCount === blocks.length) {
                                console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] All code blocks successfully highlighted.");
                                setTimeout(function() { sendPostHeight("Prism parsing finished"); }, 50);
                            }
                        });
                    });
                } else {
                    console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] No code blocks detected in this post.");
                    sendPostHeight("No code blocks found");
                }
            } else {
                console.error("[ATLAS_DEBUG] Critical Error: Prism.js is missing or failed to initialize.");
                sendPostHeight("Fallback (Prism missing)");
            }
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
        ── РЕНДЕРИНГ КОМПОНЕНТА: ПАСПОРТ ПОСТА (ВЕРХНИЙ БЛОК)
        ========================================================================== */
        function renderPassport() {
            var o = CONFIG;
            var status = (o.status || 'DRAFT').toUpperCase();
            var rt = o.readTime || (o.wordCount ? '~' + Math.ceil(Number(o.wordCount) / 200) + ' MIN' : null);

            var meta = [
                { k: 'AUTH',    v: o.author  || '—' },
                { k: 'CREATED', v: o.created || '—' }
            ];
            if (o.modified) meta.push({ k: 'LAST_MODIFIED', v: o.modified });
            if (rt)          meta.push({ k: 'READ', v: rt });

            var metaHTML = meta.map(function (m) {
                return '<span class="bp-meta-item"><b>' + m.k + '</b>: ' + m.v + '</span>';
            }).join('');

            var tags = Array.isArray(o.tags) ? o.tags : [];
            var baseUrl = o.tagBaseUrl || null;
            function toSlug(s) { return s.toLowerCase().replace(/\s+/g, '-'); }

            var tagsHTML = tags.length
                ? '<div class="bp-tags" style="padding-bottom: 14px; padding-right: 14px;">' +
                  tags.map(function (tg) {
                      return baseUrl
                          ? '<a href="' + baseUrl + toSlug(tg) + '" class="atlas-blueprint-link" target="_top">#' + tg + '</a>'
                          : '<span class="atlas-blueprint-link" style="cursor:default">#' + tg + '</span>';
                  }).join('') + '</div>'
                : '';

            document.getElementById('site-passport').innerHTML =
                '<div class="passport-bp">' +
                    '<div class="bp-title-bar">' +
                        '<div class="bp-title-bar__left">' +
                            '<span class="bp-user-prompt">' + (o.user || 'user') + '</span>' +
                            '<span style="opacity:.4">:</span>' +
                            '<span class="bp-path-prompt">' + (o.path || '~') + '</span>' +
                            '<span class="bp-root-char">#</span>' +
                            '<span class="bp-command-text">' + (o.command || 'cat log') + '</span>' +
                        '</div>' +
                        '<div class="bp-sys-status">[ SYS_STATUS: <b>' + status + '</b> ]</div>' +
                    '</div>' +
                    (o.title ? '<div class="bp-main-title">' + o.title + '</div>' : '') +
                    '<div class="bp-grid">' +
                        '<div class="bp-cell">' +
                            '<div><span class="bp-key">PROJECT</span><span class="bp-val">' + (o.project || '—') + '</span></div>' +
                            '<div><span class="bp-key">MODULE</span><span class="bp-val">'   + (o.module  || '—') + '</span></div>' +
                        '</div>' +
                        '<div class="bp-cell">' +
                            '<div><span class="bp-key">VERSION</span><span class="bp-val">' + (o.version || '—') + '</span></div>' +
                            '<div><span class="bp-key">LOG_ID</span><span class="bp-val">'  + (o.logId   || '—') + '</span></div>' +
                        '</div>' +
                    '</div>' +
                    '<div class="bp-meta">' + metaHTML + '</div>' +
                    tagsHTML +
                '</div>';
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
        ── РЕНДЕРИНГ КОМПОНЕНТА: ФУТЕР САЙТА (НИЖНИЙ БЛОК)
        ========================================================================== */
        function renderFooter(c) {
            var supportHTML = '';
            if (c.support) {
                var supportLinks = (c.support.links || []).map(function(l, idx, arr) {
                    var link = '<a href="' + l.url + '" class="atlas-blueprint-link" target="_blank">[ ' + l.text + ' ]</a>';
                    return idx < arr.length - 1
                        ? link + '<span class="atlas-footer-block__support-divider">|</span>'
                        : link;
                }).join('');

                supportHTML =
                    '<div class="atlas-footer-block__support-content">' +
                        '<div class="atlas-footer-block__support-text">' + (c.support.text || '') + '</div>' +
                        '<div class="atlas-footer-block__support-links">' + supportLinks + '</div>' +
                    '</div>';
            }

            var matrixHTML = (c.links || []).map(function(group) {
                var items = (group.items || []).map(function(item) {
                    return '<a href="' + item.url + '" class="atlas-blueprint-link" target="_blank">/ ' + item.text + '</a>';
                }).join('');

                return '<div class="atlas-footer-block__matrix-column">' +
                           '<span class="atlas-footer-block__column-label">' + group.label + '</span>' +
                           '<div class="atlas-footer-block__column-items">' + items + '</div>' +
                       '</div>';
            }).join('');

            document.getElementById('site-footer').innerHTML =
                '<div class="atlas-footer-wrapper">' +
                    '<div class="atlas-footer-block atlas-footer-block--main">' +
                        '<div class="atlas-footer-block__support-header">' +
                            '<div class="atlas-footer-block__kaomoji">' + (c.tagline || '') + '</div>' +
                            '<div class="atlas-footer-block__support-title">Let\'s stay in touch</div>' +
                        '</div>' +
                        supportHTML +
                        '<div class="atlas-footer-block__matrix-zone">' + matrixHTML + '</div>' +
                    '</div>' +
                '</div>';
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
        ── ИНИЦИАЛИЗАЦИЯ И СИНХРОНИЗАЦИЯ ДАННЫХ
        ========================================================================== */
        function applyData(d) {
            if (d.author)             CONFIG.author    = d.author;
            if (d.title)              CONFIG.title     = d.title;
            if (d.created)            CONFIG.created   = d.created;
            if (d.modified !== undefined) CONFIG.modified  = d.modified;
            if (Array.isArray(d.tags) && d.tags.length) CONFIG.tags = d.tags;

            renderPassport();
            processCodeBlocks();
        }

        // 1. Старт системы при первичной загрузке DOM
        window.addEventListener('load', function() {
            console.log("[ATLAS_DEBUG] Production Template loaded. Initializing systems...");
            renderPassport();
            processCodeBlocks(); 
        });

        // 2. Запрос метаданных из базы Wix
        (function () {
            var slug = CONFIG.slug || '';
            if (!slug) return;

            fetch(BACKEND_URL + '?slug=' + encodeURIComponent(slug))
                .then(function (r) { return r.ok ? r.json() : null; })
                .then(function (data) {
                    if (data && !data.error) applyData(data);
                    else console.warn('[ATLAS] Backend returned:', JSON.stringify(data));
                })
                .catch(function (err) { console.warn('[ATLAS] Fetch failed:', err); });
        })();

        // Резервный канал синхронизации через postMessage
        window.addEventListener('message', function (e) {
            var d = e.data;
            if (!d || d.source !== 'atlas-backend') return;
            applyData(d);
        });

        // 3. Асинхронная загрузка структуры футера
        fetch(FOOTER_URL)
            .then(function(r) { return r.ok ? r.json() : null; })
            .then(function(c) {
                if (c) {
                    renderFooter(c);
                    setTimeout(function() { sendPostHeight("Footer configuration loaded"); }, 80);
                }
            })
            .catch(function(e) { console.error('[atlas-footer-fetch]', e); });
    </script>

</body>
</html>